subject: Tennis
lead_paragraph: Top-ranked Rafael Nadal withstood 26 aces from Jo-Wilfried Tsonga to win, 6-4, 6-7 (5), 6-4, and earn a semifinals berth at the ABN Amro in Rotterdam, Netherlands. Nadal, the Australian Open champion, will meet Gaël Monfils or Julien Benneteau, who met in a later quarterfinal. Second-seeded Andy Murray also advanced against Marc Gicquel, who retired with a thigh injury after leading by 7-6 (2), 4-6, 3-0. Murray will meet the unseeded Mario Ancic.
